---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro'; import ContactCTA from '../components/ContactCTA.astro'; import artworks from '../data/artworks.json';
const get=(s)=>artworks.find(a=>a.slug===s);
const panels=[get('monday'),get('red-trike'),get('girls'),get('superman'),get('green-ball')];
---
<Layout><section class="home-hero"><div class="hero-copy"><p class="eyebrow">Established over decades / still curious</p><h1>David Jung —<br/><em>paintings, design,</em><br/>process, play.</h1><p>After decades as a designer and project manager, David Jung now mostly paints. The same eye remains: form, structure, people, objects—and the pleasure of an unexpected line.</p><div class="actions"><a class="button" href="/paintings">View the paintings</a><a href="/product_development/">Explore Product Development →</a></div></div><div class="studio-wall">{panels.map((a,i)=><a class={`panel p${i+1}`} href={`/paintings/${a.slug}/`}><img src={a.image} alt={a.alt} loading={i?'lazy':'eager'}/><span>{String(i+1).padStart(2,'0')} — {a.title}</span></a>)}<div class="wall-note">LOOK<br/>AGAIN ↘</div></div></section><section class="manifesto"><p class="eyebrow">The practice</p><p class="big-copy">A lifetime of professional design discipline, continuing as <span>playful, observant, technically skilled painting.</span></p></section><section class="three-doors"><a href="/paintings"><b>01</b><h2>Paintings</h2><p>Objects, portraits, memories and graphic mischief.</p><span>Enter gallery →</span></a><a href="/product_development/"><b>02</b><h2>Product Development</h2><p>Useful things, safer systems and better mechanisms.</p><span>Open Product Development →</span></a><a href="/project_management/"><b>03</b><h2>Project Management</h2><p>Programmes, people, constraints and delivery held together with design judgement.</p><span>Open Project Management →</span></a></section><ContactCTA/></Layout>
